Calculation of CP Current Density:
Jcp=(Io avg r+Ia tot)/A 
where: Jcp (A/㎡)=CP current density; 
Io avg r(A)=average CP rectified current output; 
Ia tot (A)=total anode current output; 
A (㎡)=total surface area of CP pipelines

Calculation of Apparent Loop Resistance:
Rl=Vr avg/Io avg r 
where: Rl (ohm)=apparent loop resistance;
Vr avg (V)=average rectified voltage output;
Io avg r (A)=average rectified current output

Calculation of Apparent Pipeline to Remote Resistance:
RC=|Ed on-Ed off|/Io avg r 
where: RC(ohm)=apparent pipeline to remote resistance;
Ed on (V)=ON potential of drain point;
Ed off (V)=OFF potential of drain point;
Io avg r (A)=average rectified current output

Calculation of Apparent Groundbed to Remote Resistance:
RD=|Ea on-Ea off|/Io avg r 
where: RD(ohm)=apparent groundbed to remote resistance;
Ea on (V)=average anodes ON potential;
Ea off (V)=average anodes OFF potential;
Io avg r (A)=average rectified current output

Calculation of CP Current Density: 
J=I/A 
where: J(A/㎡)=current density;
I(A)=current value of ac or dc;
A(㎡)=coupon surface area
